`RESEARCH-ECOMAPP-CD-CA-157343-20260411` | `RESEARCH-ECOMAPP-20260411` |\n100: | `planning-code-tasks` | `PLAN` | `PLAN-ECOMAPP-AUTH-V2-20260411` | `PLAN-ECOMAPP-CD-CA-157343-20260411` | `PLAN-ECOMAPP-20260411` |\n101: | `implementing-code` | `IMPL` | `IMPL-ECOMAPP-AUTH-V2-20260411` | `IMPL-ECOMAPP-CD-CA-157343-20260411` | `IMPL-ECOMAPP-20260411` |\n102: | `reviewing-code` | `REVIEW` | `REVIEW-ECOMAPP-AUTH-V2-20260411` | `REVIEW-ECOMAPP-CD-CA-157343-20260411` | `REVIEW-ECOMAPP-20260411` |\n103: | `fixing-bugs` | `QUICKFIX` | `QUICKFIX-ECOMAPP-BUG-002-20260411` | `QUICKFIX-ECOMAPP-QUICK-FIX-20260411` | `QUICKFIX-ECOMAPP-20260411` |\n104: \n105: **FEATURE_SLUG derivation (deterministic, no LLM judgement):**\n106: - Lowercase the feature_id, then replace any run of non-alphanumerics with a single hyphen.\n107: - Strip leading/trailing hyphens.\n108: - Truncate to 32 chars.\n109: - Then UPPERCASE the slug for the SESSION_ID (matches the `{PROJECT_NAME_UPPER}` style).\n110: - Examples: `\"FEAT LAC Android v2\"` → `FEAT-LAC-ANDROID-V2`. `\"i18n_pack\"` → `I18N-PACK`. `\"a/b/c\"` → `A-B-C`.\n111: \n112: **SESSION_NAME pass-through:**\n113: - The runtime supplies session_name verbatim via the capability prompt; do not re-format. Preserve hyphens and case as given. (e.g., `cd-CA-157343` stays `cd-CA-157343` in the SESSION_ID — uppercased only in the final concatenation when the rest of the ID is uppercased.)\n114: \n115: **Rules:**\n116: - Set once at initialization. Never changes within a session.\n117: - REPAIR mode reuses the existing SESSION_ID from the prior run — do NOT generate a new one. To recover the prior SESSION_ID, parse it from the existing spec filename in the input/output folder (preferred) or from the IMPL-STATE header.\n118:   - **In REPAIR, NEVER call `date()`/`today()`/`time()` or recompute the SESSION_ID from parameters.** The date segment is fixed at BUILD time and is immutable across every iteration of the same artifact; minting a fresh date produces a SECOND file (e.g. `…-20260605.md` vs `…-20260610.md`) instead of overwriting the original — the documented duplicate-on-REPAIR defect.\n119:   - **Recovery algorithm:** glob the recorded output folder for the artifact (`<PREFIX>-*.md`); from the matched filename extract the SESSION_ID as the substring between `<PREFIX>-` and `.md`; reuse it verbatim for every write. If multiple match, pick the most recently modified. If a repair target was named but no file matches → see §7 (ABORT, do not BUILD).\n120: - The SESSION_ID propagates verbatim into every artifact filename listed in this protocol (`RESEARCH-SPEC-{SESSION_ID}.md`, `PLAN-SPEC-{SESSION_ID}.md`, `IMPL-STATE-{SESSION_ID}.md`, `REVIEW-SPEC-{SESSION_ID}.md`, etc.). Filenames are the primary collision-prevention surface — do NOT shorten or omit the SESSION_ID in any output filename.\n121: \n122: **Why this format:** Prior runs that used `{TYPE}-{PROJECT}-{YYYYMMDD}` collided when two sessions ran on the same project on the same day, silently overwriting each other's specs. Including feature_id (or session_name as a fallback) keeps every concurrent or sequential run uniquely addressable in the same project folder.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## 2. _progress.json — Early Signal Write\n127: \n128: **Purpose:** Prevents the orchestrator coordinator from sending SIGINT to a running skill.\n129: \n130: Write this as the **FIRST file action** in any skill execution (before creating any other outputs):\n131: \n132: ```json\n133: {\n134:   \"skill\": \"{skill-name}\",\n135:   \"session_id\": \"{SESSION_ID}\",\n136:   \"status\": \"RUNNING\",\n137:   \"started_at\": \"{ISO timestamp}\",\n138:   \"completed_at\": null,\n139:   \"total\": 0,\n140:   \"completed\": 0,\n141:   \"items\": []\n142: }\n143: ```\n144: \n145: Write to: `{output_folder}/_progress.json`\n146: \n147: **Update cadence:**\n148: - On FIC trigger (Section 5): `\"status\": \"COMPACTION_NEEDED\"`\n149: - On completion: `\"status\": \"COMPLETED\"`, `\"completed_at\": \"{ISO timestamp}\"`\n150: - On failure: `\"status\": \"FAILED\"`, `\"completed_at\": \"{ISO timestamp}\"`\n151: \n152: **Schema variants.** A skill picks ONE shape based on its work model. The common\n153: envelope (`skill`, `session_id`, `status`, `started_at`, `completed_at`) is identical\n154: across variants.\n155: \n156: - **List shape (default — shown above)** — uses `total`, `completed`, `items[]`. Suits\n157:   skills that produce many discrete artifacts (e.g. `implementing-code` writing source\n158:   files; `planning-code-tasks` tracking task entries).\n159: - **Section shape** — uses `skeleton_written` (bool) + `sections{}` map. Suits skills\n160:   that produce a single multi-section spec file from large unstructured inputs. See\n161:   **Section 10** for the full protocol (skeleton-first + one-section-per-write +\n162:   source extraction + CONTINUE re-entry).\n163: \n164: ### Skill-Level Enforcement (FIRST ACTION / LAST ACTION)\n165: \n166: Every skill MUST include these two inline callouts — agents do not reliably follow\n167: protocol-only references for session bookend writes:\n168: \n169: **At session start** (after folder creation, before any other file write):\n170: \n171: > **FIRST ACTION — MANDATORY:** Write `_progress.json` to the output folder before any other file write.\n172: > This prevents the orchestrator from sending SIGINT.\n173: \n174: Include the minimal JSON schema inline in the skill so the agent can write immediately\n175: without reading this file first. Use `\"session_id\": \"initializing\"` as placeholder.\n176: \n177: **At session end** (after all spec files written, after Memory Bank writes):\n178: \n179: > **LAST ACTION — MANDATORY:** Update `_progress.json` status to `COMPLETED` with `completed_at` timestamp.\n180: > If the session failed, set status to `FAILED` instead.\n181: \n182: These callouts are NOT infrastructure duplication — they are the minimum viable bridge\n183: between protocol and agent behavior. The full lifecycle lives here; the callouts trigger it.\n184: \n185: **For `implementing-code` only** — also include `output_contract` (survives compaction):\n186: \n187: ```json\n188: {\n189:   \"skill\": \"implementing-code\",\n190:   \"session_id\": \"{SESSION_ID}\",\n191:   \"status\": \"RUNNING\",\n192:   \"output_contract\": {\n193:     \"progress_folder_path\": \"{progress_folder_path}\",\n194:     \"impl_state_file\": \"IMPL-STATE-{session_id}.md\",\n195:     \"source_path\": \"{source_path}\",\n196:     \"expected_outputs\": [\"source_path\", \"impl_state_path\"]\n197:   }\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: Pin the same values in the IMPL-STATE header under `output_contract`. After context\n202: compaction, read IMPL-STATE header (not filesystem) to recover the output path and format.\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## 3. IMPL-STATE Schema (implementing-code only)\n207: \n208: Single consolidated tracking file. Written at Phase A as skeleton tables (header + separator\n209: rows only — no example data). Rows appended after each file write using EOL append mode —\n210: never rewrite or replace the whole file. Use Edit tool to insert at end of table.\n211: \n212: ```\n213: IMPL_INDEX = {\n214:   session_id: string,\n215:   project_name: string,\n216:   source_path: string,\n217:   project_root: string,             // same as source_path\n218:   mode: \"STANDARD\" | \"REPAIR\",\n219:   input_format: \"AGENT_NATIVE\" | \"LEGACY\",\n220:   active_phase: string,\n221:   output_contract: {\n222:     progress_folder_path: string,\n223:     impl_state_file: string,\n224:     source_path: string,\n225:     expected_outputs: [string]\n226:   },\n227:   phases: [{ id, status, started_at, completed_at, files_count, tests_count }],\n228:   files_touched: [{ phase, path, action, status, test_file }],\n229:   repair_log: [{ iteration, phase, feedback, files_modified: [{ path, change_summary }] }],\n230:   blockers: [{ phase, description, timestamp, resolution }],\n231:   deviations: [{ phase, description, reason, impact }],\n232:   build_commands_discovered: [],\n233:   tech_stack_detected: {},\n234:   tool_results: {},\n235:   execution_log: [],\n236:   metrics: {},\n237:   validations: {},\n238:   open_questions: []\n239: }\n240: ```\n241: \n242: **BLOCKING gate:** Do NOT generate the next file until the files_touched append has been\n243: confirmed as a completed tool call. Batching updates = lost progress on interruption.\n244: \n245: ### 3.1 IMPL-STATE Write Budget (anti-heartbeat-churn)\n246: \n247: IMPL-STATE writes are limited to:\n248:   (a) skeleton write at Phase A start,\n249:   (b) one append per file completed in Phase B (already required by the §3 BLOCKING gate),\n250:   (c) one write at each phase boundary,\n251:   (d) one final write at end.\n252: \n253: Total writes per run MUST satisfy:\n254: \n255:     writes_to_IMPL_STATE  <=  files_touched + phases + 2\n256: \n257: All Phase B writes MUST be APPEND-MODE row inserts into `files_touched`.\n258: Full-file rewrites of IMPL-STATE between sub-phases are FORBIDDEN.\n259: \n260: Self-check before any IMPL-STATE write:\n261: \n262:     heartbeat_ratio = existing_IMPL_STATE_writes / source_or_test_files_written_so_far\n263:     IF heartbeat_ratio > 2.0 → skip this write. Resume only after the next\n264:     source/test file is written.\n265: \n266: Rationale: every IMPL-STATE write consumes one agent iteration. Excess\n267: heartbeats are the leading cause of iteration-cap exhaustion before the\n268: final sub-phase of medium-sized implementations.\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ## 4. Memory Bank — Cross-Session Continuity\n273: \n274: Two files in `./context-pack/` provide every session's agent with immediate context\n275: about what happened before — without re-reading all prior session artifacts.\n276: \n277: ```\n278: context-pack/\n279: ├── active-context.md    ← \"What is happening NOW?\" (overwritten each session)\n280: └── progress.md          ← \"What HAS been accomplished?\" (append-only ledger)\n281: ```\n282: \n283: Both live at the **project root** `./context-pack/` — shared across all capabilities\n284: so `progress.md` becomes a unified cross-capability timeline.\n285: \n286: ### RULE 10 — active-context.md (Session Lifecycle)\n287: \n288: At SESSION START: write `context-pack/active-context.md` with current session ID,\n289: scope, and any prior session context loaded above. Status: `STARTING`.\n290: At SESSION END: overwrite with final state (status, decisions, blockers, key artifacts).\n291: If the session crashes before finalization, the SESSION START write provides\n292: \"where we were\" context for the next session.\n293: \n294: ### RULE 11 — progress.md (Per-Phase Milestone Ledger)\n295: \n296: After EVERY phase completes (NOT just the final phase): append one milestone row to\n297: `context-pack/progress.md` (append-only — never overwrite, never delete prior rows).\n298: Writing IMPL-STATE does NOT satisfy this write — they are different files with different\n299: scopes. Skipping an intermediate phase write breaks per-phase crash recovery.\n300: \n301: ### Session Start\n302: \n303: ```\n304: CONTEXT_PACK_PATH = ./context-pack\n305: \n306: IF exists({CONTEXT_PACK_PATH}/active-context.md):\n307:   READ active-context.md\n308:   EXTRACT: prior_session_id, status, current_focus, open_blockers, decisions_log\n309:   LOG: \"Memory Bank: loaded active-context from session {prior_session_id}\"\n310:   # Use to: avoid re-discovering known blockers, continue from prior state,\n311:   #         respect decisions already made (do not contradict them)\n312: ELSE:\n313:   LOG: \"Memory Bank: No active-context.md found. First session.\"\n314: \n315: IF exists({CONTEXT_PACK_PATH}/progress.md):\n316:   READ progress.md\n317:   EXTRACT: milestone_count, last_milestone\n318: ELSE:\n319:   LOG: \"Memory Bank: No progress.md found. First session.\"\n320: \n321: # Write active-context.md at session START (crash recovery — mandatory)\n322: WRITE {CONTEXT_PACK_PATH}/active-context.md:\n323:   ---\n324:   document_type: active-context\n325:   session_id: {SESSION_ID}\n326:   capability: {capability_name}\n327:   skill: {skill_name}\n328:   project: {project_name}\n329:   last_updated: {ISO timestamp}\n330:   status: STARTING\n331:   ---\n332:   # Active Context: {project_name}\n333:   ## Current Focus\n334:   Session {SESSION_ID} initializing. Skill: {skill_name}. Mode: {BUILD | REPAIR}.\n335:   ## Prior Session Context\n336:   {IF prior loaded: Previous: {prior_session_id} — status: {prior_status}. Include blockers/decisions.}\n337:   {ELSE: First session — no prior context.}\n338:   ## Open Blockers\n339:   {Copy from prior session if any, else \"None.\"}\n340: ```\n341: \n342: ### Session End\n343: \n344: ```\n345: # 1. Overwrite active-context.md with final state\n346: WRITE {CONTEXT_PACK_PATH}/active-context.md:\n347:   ---\n348:   status: {COMPLETED | FAILED | BLOCKED}\n349:   session_id: {SESSION_ID}\n350:   last_updated: {ISO timestamp}\n351:   ---\n352:   # Active Context: {project_name}\n353:   ## Current Focus\n354:   {COMPLETED: \"{skill_name} complete. Produced: {artifact summary with counts}.\"}\n355:   {FAILED: \"{skill_name} failed. Reason: {description}.\"}\n356:   {BLOCKED: \"{skill_name} blocked. Blocker: {description}. Required: {resolution}.\"}\n357:   ## Decisions Log\n358:   Append-only within a session. Preserve ALL rows from prior sessions.\n359:   | ID | Decision | Rationale | Impact | Reversible | Session |\n360:   |----|----------|-----------|--------|------------|---------|\n361:   {Carry forward all prior rows. Append new decisions from this session.}\n362:   {ID format: D-{NNN}, sequential across sessions, never reset.}\n363:   {If no new decisions: keep prior rows, add nothing.}\n364:   ## Open Blockers\n365:   {Unresolved issues, or \"No open blockers.\"}\n366:   ## Key Artifacts\n367:   | Artifact | Path | Status |\n368:   |----------|------|--------|\n369:   | {primary output} | {path} | written |\n370: \n371: # 2. Append milestone to progress.md\n372: IF NOT exists({CONTEXT_PACK_PATH}/progress.md):\n373:   CREATE with header:\n374:     ---\n375:     document_type: progress-ledger\n376:     project: {project_name}\n377:     created_at: {ISO timestamp}\n378:     ---\n379:     # Progress Ledger: {project_name}\n380:     | Session | Date | Capability | Skill | Status | Artifacts | Notes |\n381:     |---------|------|------------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n382: \n383: APPEND one row:\n384:   | {SESSION_ID} | {date} | {capability} | {skill_name} | {STATUS} | {N <artifact-type>} | {1-line note} |\n385:   # {N <artifact-type>} MUST use the specific type from the registry below.\n386:   # Examples: \"12 tasks (4 phases)\", \"48 files, 32 tests\", \"17 review-findings\"\n387:   # NEVER write: \"1 artifact\", \"N artifacts\", or leave blank.\n388: ```\n389: \n390: Both writes are **MANDATORY** — even on failure, record the failure state.\n391: \n392: ### Verification After Writing progress.md\n393: \n394: ```\n395: VERIFY exists(context-pack/progress.md)\n396: IF NOT exists: LOG \"ERROR: write FAILED. Retrying.\" → RETRY (mandatory tool call)\n397: IF still fails: LOG \"CRITICAL: Memory Bank write failed. Manual intervention required.\"\n398: \n399: READ last line — VERIFY it contains SESSION_ID AND specific artifact count (not \"N artifacts\")\n400: IF generic: REWRITE the row with the correct count from the registry.\n401: \n402: LOG: \"Memory Bank: progress.md verified — {N} rows. Last: {SESSION_ID} | {artifact_count}\"\n403: ```\n404: \n405: This verification is **NON-NEGOTIABLE**.\n406: \n407: ### Artifact Type Registry\n408: \n409: | Skill | Artifact Type | Example |\n410: |-------|--------------|---------|\n411: | `researching-adrs` | ADRs | `12 ADRs` |\n412: | `researching-bounded-contexts` | bounded-contexts | `7 bounded-contexts` |\n413: | `establishing-architecture-foundation` | services | `9 services` |\n414: | `specifying-architecture` | architecture-docs | `3 architecture-docs` |\n415: | `researching-prd` | requirements | `24 requirements` |\n416: | `planning-epics` | epics | `15 epics` |\n417: | `implementing-user-stories` | user-stories | `48 user-stories` |\n418: | `researching-code-design` | research-docs | `20 research-docs` |\n419: | `planning-code-tasks` | tasks | `12 tasks (4 phases)` |\n420: | `implementing-code` | source-files + tests | `48 files, 32 tests` |\n421: | `reviewing-code` | review-findings | `17 review-findings` |\n422: | `adversarial-platform-review` | conformance-findings | `4 conformance-findings (B1-B4 BLOCKER)` |\n423: | `generating-test-cases` | test-cases | `35 test-cases` |\n424: | `generating-e2e-test-cases` | E2E-test-cases | `22 E2E-test-cases` |\n425: | `creating-qe-master-plan` | test-domains | `8 test-domains` |\n426: | `benchmarking-execution` | benchmark-results | `1 benchmark-results` |\n427: | `db-migration-quality-planning` | migration-test-domains | `5 migration-test-domains` |\n428: | `db-parity-execution` | parity-diff-tables | `180 parity-diff-tables` |\n429: | `db-source-profiling` | profiled-tables | `210 profiled-tables` |\n430: | `defining-qe-strategy` | strategy-sections | `6 strategy-sections` |\n431: | `formatting-platform-export` | work-items | `63 work-items` |\n432: | `secreview-intake-validation` | validated-intake-package | `1 validated_intake_package` |\n433: | `calibrating-catalog` | catalog-entries | `14 catalog-entries` |\n434: | `creating-test-master-plan` | test-plan-sections | `10 test-plan-sections` |\n435: | `analyzing-impact` | impacted-tests | `18 impacted-tests` |\n436: | `developing-test-scripts` | test-scripts | `12 test-scripts` |\n437: | `executing-automation` | executed-tests | `25 executed-tests` |\n438: | `secreview-context-correlation` | service-graph-elements | `14 service-graph-elements` |\n439: | `secreview-finding-enrichment` | validated-findings | `10 validated_finding records, P1–P4 register` |\n440: | `secreview-report-generation` | report-pdfs | `2 report PDFs (technical + executive); case Closed` |\n441: | `executing-tests` | executed-tests | `30 executed-tests` |\n442: | `scoping-engagement-baseline` | scope-baseline-rows | `18 baseline rows across 4 capabilities` |\n443: | `estimating-supervision` | supervision-plan | `4.5 FTE across 5 roles, 6 months (pre_screening)` |\n444: | `assembling-estimation-proposal` | proposal + internal-audit | `1 proposal + 1 internal-audit (margin 2.4x)` |\n445: | `interviewing-code` | knowledge-graphs | `1 knowledge-graphs` |\n446: | `validating-code-interview` | analysis-reports | `1 analysis-reports` |\n447: | `designing-structure` | documentation-outlines | `1 documentation-outlines` |\n448: | `discovering-kit-templates` | template-candidates | `5 template-candidates` |\n449: | `scaffolding-kit-extensions` | resolved-extensions | `14 resolved-extensions` |\n450: | `secreview-static-scanning` | consolidated-findings | `42 consolidated-findings across 3 repos` |\n451: | `generating-omniverse-boilerplate` | source-files | `9 files, 3 tests` |\n452: | `generating-content` | draft-documentation | `1 draft-documentation` |\n453: | `refining-iteratively` | refined-documentation | `1 refined-documentation` |\n454: | `reverse-engineering-product` | discovery-deliverables | `11 discovery-deliverables (FRD, intent, flows, data-model, tokens-raw, tokens-coverage, audit, selectors, text-inventory, behaviors-catalog, figma-tokens.json)` |\n455: | `coverage-gap-analyzer` | coverage-reports | `2 coverage-reports (gap-report-{date}-{project}.md, recommended-tcs-{date}-{project}.md)` |\n456: | `coverage-judge` | coverage-reports | `1 coverage-reports (final-coverage-report-{date}-{project}.md)` |\n457: | `pentest-intake-normalization` | engagement-intake | `1 engagement-intake (10 sections)` |\n458: | `pentest-scope-validation` | authorized-scope-register | `1 authorized-scope-register` |\n459: | `pentest-asset-verification` | asset-verification-evidence | `1 asset-verification-evidence` |\n460: | `pentest-roe-assembly` | roe-package | `1 roe-package (7-gate checklist)` |\n461: | `pentest-recon-planning` | recon-plan | `1 recon-plan` |\n462: | `pentest-surface-enumeration` | attack-surface-findings | `1 attack-surface-map + N findings` |\n463: | `pentest-technology-fingerprinting` | technology-fingerprint | `1 technology-fingerprint` |\n464: | `pentest-scope-boundary-flagging` | public-exposure-findings | `N public-exposure-findings` |\n465: | `pentest-webapi-test-planning` | webapi-test-plan | `1 webapi-test-plan` |\n466: | `pentest-auth-session-testing` | auth-session-findings | `N auth-session-findings` |\n467: | `pentest-owasp-web-testing` | web-findings | `N web-findings` |\n468: | `pentest-owasp-api-testing` | api-findings | `N api-findings` |\n469: | `pentest-ai-asset-mapping` | ai-asset-map | `1 ai-asset-map` |\n470: | `pentest-prompt-injection-testing` | prompt-injection-findings | `N prompt-injection-findings` |\n471: | `pentest-rag-memory-testing` | rag-memory-findings | `N rag-memory-findings` |\n472: | `pentest-tool-mcp-testing` | tool-mcp-findings | `N tool-mcp-findings` |\n473: | `pentest-ai-resource-exhaustion-testing` | ai-resource-findings | `N ai-resource-findings` |\n474: | `pentest-mobile-scoping` | mobile-asset-map | `1 mobile-asset-map` |\n475: | `pentest-mobile-static-analysis` | binary-analysis-findings | `N binary-analysis-findings` |\n476: | `pentest-mobile-dynamic-analysis` | mobile-runtime-findings | `N mobile-runtime-findings` |\n477: | `pentest-mobile-auth-transport-testing` | platform-misconfig-findings | `N platform-misconfig-findings` |\n478: | `pentest-infra-enumeration` | network-service-inventory | `1 network-service-inventory` |\n479: | `pentest-infra-misconfig-testing` | infrastructure-exposure-findings | `N infrastructure-exposure-findings` |\n480: | `pentest-infra-impact-summary` | perimeter-risk-summary | `1 perimeter-risk-summary` |\n481: | `pentest-poc-planning` | poc-plan | `1 poc-plan` |\n482: | `pentest-poc-execution` | validated-poc-evidence | `N validated-poc-evidence` |\n483: | `pentest-exploit-chain-analysis` | exploit-chain-analysis | `N exploit-chain-analysis` |\n484: | `pentest-post-exploitation` | post-exploitation-findings | `N post-exploitation-findings` |\n485: | `pentest-blast-radius-assessment` | blast-radius-assessment | `1 blast-radius-assessment` |\n486: | `pentest-poc-evidence-packaging` | signed-poc-package | `1 signed-poc-package + retest-scripts` |\n487: | `pentest-finding-consolidation` | consolidated-findings | `1 consolidated-findings` |\n488: | `pentest-severity-taxonomy-mapping` | cvss-cwe-owasp-mapping | `N cvss-cwe-owasp-mapping` |\n489: | `pentest-compliance-mapping` | compliance-control-matrix | `1 compliance-control-matrix` |\n490: | `pentest-report-generation` | security-report | `2 reports (executive, technical)` |\n491: | `pentest-evidence-signing` | signed-evidence-package | `1 signed-evidence-package` |\n492: | `pentest-remediation-prioritization` | remediation-roadmap | `1 remediation-roadmap` |\n493: | `pentest-remediation-guidance` | remediation-guidance | `N remediation-guidance` |\n494: | `pentest-remediation-register` | remediation-status-register | `1 remediation-status-register` |\n495: | `pentest-retest-validation` | retest-results | `N retest-results` |\n496: | `secreview-memory-synthesis` | scan-memory-entries | `N memory entries` |\n497: | `verifying-artifacts` | verification-reports | `1 verification-reports` |\n498: \n499: If your skill is not listed: count the PRIMARY deliverable artifacts and use a descriptive plural type.\n\n[File truncated at 500 lines for safety. Use offset/limit to paginate.]", "metadata": {"start_line": 1, "end_line": 500, "returned_lines": 500, "has_more": true, "eof_reached": false, "truncated": true}}}
