\n332: - when: user clicks on a character card\n333: - then: highlight selected character and show additional information\n334: - given: character is selected\n335: - when: user clicks another character\n336: - then: update selection to new character and hide previous details\n337: **Priority:** Should Have\n338: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:40-44\n339: \n340: ## Non-Functional Requirements\n341: \n342: ### NFR-01: Browser Compatibility\n343: **Description:** Application must function across modern web browsers.\n344: **Metric:** Browser support matrix compliance\n345: **Target:** Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Safari 14+, Edge 90+ with full feature support\n346: **Measurement Method:** Automated cross-browser testing with compatibility matrix validation\n347: **Priority:** Must Have\n348: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:140-148\n349: \n350: ### NFR-02: Performance Loading Time\n351: **Description:** Fast initial page load for optimal user experience.\n352: **Metric:** Page load time\n353: **Target:** < 3 seconds for complete application load\n354: **Measurement Method:** Performance monitoring tools (Lighthouse, WebPageTest)\n355: **Priority:** Must Have\n356: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:128-133\n357: \n358: ### NFR-03: Responsive Design\n359: **Description:** Application must adapt to different viewport sizes.\n360: **Metric:** Layout adaptation at break points\n361: **Target:** Functional layout at 820px+ viewport width\n362: **Measurement Method:** Visual regression testing across viewport sizes\n363: **Priority:** Must Have\n364: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:70-74\n365: \n366: ### NFR-04: Animation Performance\n367: **Description:** Smooth visual transitions and hover effects.\n368: **Metric:** Frames per second for animations\n369: **Target:** 60fps CSS transitions for all interactive elements\n370: **Measurement Method:** Chrome DevTools Performance profiler\n371: **Priority:** Should Have\n372: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:135-139\n373: \n374: ### NFR-05: Client-Side Security\n375: **Description:** Protection against common web vulnerabilities.\n376: **Metric:** Security vulnerability assessment\n377: **Target:** OWASP Top 10 compliance through static analysis scanning\n378: **Measurement Method:** Automated security scanning (SAST tools)\n379: **Priority:** Must Have\n380: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:155-162\n381: \n382: ### NFR-06: Code Quality Standards\n383: **Description:** Maintainable, well-documented educational code.\n384: **Metric:** Code analysis metrics\n385: **Target:** 90%+ code documentation coverage, modular component structure\n386: **Measurement Method:** Code analysis tools, peer review checklists\n387: **Priority:** Should Have\n388: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:121-126\n389: \n390: ### NFR-07: Search Performance\n391: **Description:** Efficient real-time filtering of character data.\n392: **Metric:** Filter response time\n393: **Target:** < 100ms response time for search operations on 8 character dataset\n394: **Measurement Method:** Performance profiling of search/filter functions\n395: **Priority:** Should Have\n396: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:135-139\n397: \n398: ### NFR-08: Visual Design Consistency\n399: **Description:** Consistent Star Wars themed visual appearance.\n400: **Metric:** Design system compliance\n401: **Target:** 100% compliance with specified color palette and typography\n402: **Measurement Method:** Visual regression testing against design specifications\n403: **Priority:** Should Have\n404: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:62-69\n405: \n406: ## KPIs\n407: \n408: ### KPI-01: Learning Engagement Rate\n409: **Description:** Measure of user interaction with educational features.\n410: **Metric:** Interaction events per session\n411: **Target:** Average 10+ interactions per user session\n412: **Measurement Method:** Track user clicks, searches, and feature usage\n413: **Priority:** Must Have\n414: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:16-21\n415: \n416: ### KPI-02: Concept Demonstration Effectiveness\n417: **Description:** Success rate of JavaScript concepts demonstration.\n418: **Metric:** Completion rate of interactive exercises\n419: **Target:** 80% of users complete at least one full interaction cycle\n420: **Measurement Method:** Track user journey completion paths\n421: **Priority:** Should Have\n422: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:16-21\n423: \n424: ### KPI-03: Search Functionality Usage\n425: **Description:** Frequency of character search feature usage.\n426: **Metric:** Search queries per session\n427: **Target:** Average 3+ search queries per active session\n428: **Measurement Method:** Track search input events and result interactions\n429: **Priority:** Should Have\n430: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:45-48\n431: \n432: ### KPI-04: Performance Accessibility\n433: **Description:** Load time performance across different network conditions.\n434: **Metric:** Load time compliance percentage\n435: **Target:** 95% of sessions load within 3-second target\n436: **Measurement Method:** Real User Monitoring (RUM) data collection\n437: **Priority:** Must Have\n438: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:128-133\n439: \n440: ### KPI-05: Browser Compatibility Coverage\n441: **Description:** Success rate across supported browser matrix.\n442: **Metric:** Browser success rate\n443: **Target:** 98% functionality success across Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge\n444: **Measurement Method:** Automated cross-browser testing and error reporting\n445: **Priority:** Must Have\n446: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:140-148\n447: \n448: ### KPI-06: Code Learning Retention\n449: **Description:** User retention of demonstrated programming concepts.\n450: **Metric:** Return visit frequency\n451: **Target:** 40% of users return within 7 days for additional practice\n452: **Measurement Method:** User session tracking and analytics\n453: **Priority:** Could Have\n454: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:115-119\n455: \n456: ## Jobs-To-Be-Done (JTBD)\n457: \n458: ### JTBD-01: Learn JavaScript Fundamentals\n459: **Who:** Beginner JavaScript Student (P-01)\n460: **What:** Master practical JavaScript ES6+ concepts through hands-on interaction\n461: **Why:** Bridge the gap between theoretical knowledge and real-world application development\n462: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:16-18\n463: \n464: ### JTBD-02: Understand Vue.js Reactivity\n465: **Who:** Web Development Learner (P-02)\n466: **What:** Learn Vue.js 2.x data binding and component patterns through interactive examples\n467: **Why:** Apply modern frontend development framework knowledge to practical projects\n468: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:18-19\n469: \n470: ### JTBD-03: Practice DOM Manipulation\n471: **Who:** Beginner JavaScript Student (P-01)\n472: **What:** Gain experience with dynamic HTML element modification and event handling\n473: **Why:** Build confidence in creating interactive web applications beyond static pages\n474: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:20\n475: \n476: ### JTBD-04: Demonstrate Programming Concepts to Students\n477: **Who:** Programming Educator (P-03)\n478: **What:** Use engaging interactive examples to teach abstract programming concepts\n479: **Why:** Increase student engagement and comprehension through practical, relatable examples\n480: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:14-15\n481: \n482: ### JTBD-05: Apply ES6+ Features Practically\n483: **Who:** Web Development Learner (P-02)\n484: **What:** Practice using arrow functions, array methods, and object patterns in real scenarios\n485: **Why:** Transition from theoretical knowledge to practical coding ability\n486: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:44-50\n487: \n488: ### JTBD-06: Create Portfolio-Worthy Projects\n489: **Who:** Web Development Learner (P-02)\n490: **What:** Build interactive components that demonstrate modern web development skills\n491: **Why:** Create evidence of practical ability for job applications and career advancement\n492: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:14-15\n493: \n494: ## Traceability\n495: \n496: ### Forward Traceability (FR → JTBD)\n497: \n498: | FR ID | JTBD ID(s) | Status |\n499: |-------|------------|--------|\n500: | FR-01 | JTBD-01, JTBD-03, JTBD-05 | mapped |\n\n[File truncated at 500 lines for safety. Use offset/limit to paginate.]", "metadata": {"start_line": 1, "end_line": 500, "returned_lines": 500, "has_more": true, "eof_reached": false, "truncated": true}}}
