ts**: Star Wars Lego character images\n546: - **Dependency Type:** Technical\n547: - **Impact:** Core application content\n548: - **Failure Mode:** Broken image display\n549: - **Mitigation:** Include default placeholder images\n550: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:95-98\n551: \n552: ### Internal Dependencies\n553: **Vue.js 2.x Framework**: Core application framework\n554: - **Dependency Type:** Technical\n555: - **Impact:** Application functionality\n556: - **Failure Mode:** Complete application failure\n557: - **Mitigation:** Include local Vue.js library fallback\n558: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:51-82\n559: \n560: **Modern Browser Support**: ES6+ JavaScript feature support\n561: - **Dependency Type:** Organizational\n562: - **Impact:** Feature availability\n563: - **Failure Mode:** Limited or broken functionality\n564: - **Mitigation:** Provide browser compatibility warnings\n565: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:140-154\n566: \n567: **Internet Connectivity**: Required for external resource loading\n568: - **Dependency Type:** Organizational\n569: - **Impact:** Fonts and optional features\n570: - **Failure Mode:** Degraded visual experience\n571: - **Mitigation:** Graceful degradation to system fonts\n572: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:88-90\n573: \n574: ## Risks\n575: \n576: ### RSK-01: External CDN Unavailability\n577: **Description:** Google Fonts or Material Symbols CDN may be unavailable.\n578: **Likelihood:** Low\n579: **Impact:** Medium (degraded visual experience)\n580: **Mitigation:** Local font fallbacks and CSS system font specifications\n581: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:30-31\n582: \n583: ### RSK-02: Browser Compatibility Issues\n584: **Description:** Modern JavaScript features may not work consistently across all target browsers.\n585: **Likelihood:** Medium\n586: **Impact:** High (broken functionality)\n587: **Mitigation:** Comprehensive cross-browser testing and progressive enhancement\n588: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:140-154\n589: \n590: ### RSK-03: Performance Degradation\n591: **Description:** Complex animations and interactions may impact performance on lower-end devices.\n592: **Likelihood:** Low\n593: **Impact:** Medium (poor user experience)\n594: **Mitigation:** Performance profiling and optimization of critical rendering paths\n595: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:128-139\n596: \n597: ### RSK-04: Asset Loading Failures\n598: **Description:** Character images or other assets may fail to load properly.\n599: **Likelihood:** Medium\n600: **Impact:** Medium (incomplete user experience)\n601: **Mitigation:** Error handling and fallback content strategies\n602: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:95-98\n603: \n604: ### RSK-05: Learning Effectiveness Gap\n605: **Description:** Interactive elements may not effectively teach intended programming concepts.\n606: **Likelihood:** Medium\n607: **Impact:** High (fails primary objective)\n608: **Mitigation:** User testing and educational content validation\n609: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:16-21\n610: \n611: ## Assumptions\n612: \n613: ### ASM-01: Technical Literacy\n614: **Assumption:** Target users have basic computer literacy and can operate web browsers.\n615: **Impact:** If false, users may struggle with basic navigation and interaction.\n616: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:14-15\n617: \n618: ### ASM-02: Internet Access\n619: **Assumption:** Users have reliable internet access for loading external resources.\n620: **Impact:** If false, fonts and icons may not load, affecting visual design.\n621: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:88-90\n622: \n623: ### ASM-03: Viewport Availability\n624: **Assumption:** Users have access to devices with 820px+ screen resolution.\n625: **Impact:** If false, users cannot access the application as designed.\n626: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:70-74\n627: \n628: ### ASM-04: JavaScript Interest\n629: **Assumption:** Target users are motivated to learn JavaScript programming concepts.\n630: **Impact:** If false, engagement metrics may be lower than anticipated.\n631: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:16-18\n632: \n633: ## Constraints\n634: \n635: ### CNS-01: Browser Support Matrix\n636: **Constraint:** Must support Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Safari 14+, Edge 90+\n637: **Type:** Technical\n638: **Justification:** Modern JavaScript ES6+ feature requirements\n639: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:140-148\n640: \n641: ### CNS-02: Minimum Viewport Width\n642: **Constraint:** Application only supports viewports 820px and wider\n643: **Type:** Technical\n644: **Justification:** Desktop and tablet focus, no mobile support\n645: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:70-80\n646: \n647: ### CNS-03: Client-Side Only Architecture\n648: **Constraint:** No backend or database integration in current scope\n649: **Type:** Technical\n650: **Justification:** Pure client-side educational application design\n651: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:88-91\n652: \n653: ### CNS-04: External Resource Dependency\n654: **Constraint:** Google Fonts require internet connectivity\n655: **Type:** Technical\n656: **Justification:** Typography design requirements\n657: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:88-90\n658: \n659: ## MVP Phasing\n660: \n661: ### MVP Phase 0: Core Functionality\n662: **Scope:**\n663: - FR-01: Character Gallery Display\n664: - FR-02: Character Search System\n665: - NFR-01: Browser Compatibility\n666: - NFR-02: Performance Loading Time\n667: **Priority:** Must Have features for basic educational value\n668: **Duration:** Foundation phase\n669: \n670: ### MVP Phase 1: Interactive Features\n671: **Scope:**\n672: - FR-03: Character Like/Favorite System\n673: - FR-04: Character Deletion System\n674: - FR-07: Interactive Character Selection\n675: - NFR-04: Animation Performance\n676: **Priority:** Should Have features for enhanced engagement\n677: **Prerequisite:** Phase 0 complete\n678: \n679: ### MVP Phase 2: Personalization\n680: **Scope:**\n681: - FR-05: Personalized Greeting System\n682: - FR-06: Dynamic Title Updates\n683: - NFR-06: Code Quality Standards\n684: **Priority:** Could Have features for advanced user experience\n685: **Prerequisite:** Phase 1 complete\n686: \n687: ## Glossary\n688: \n689: ### SPA (Single Page Application)\n690: **Definition:** A web application that loads a single HTML page and dynamically updates content as the user interacts.\n691: **Source:** context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:34\n692: \n693: ### Vue.js\n694: **Definition:** A progressive JavaScript framework for building user interfaces with reactive data binding.\n695: **Source:** context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:29\n696: \n697: ### ES6+/ECMAScript 2015+\n698: **Definition:** Modern JavaScript standard with features like arrow functions, classes, and enhanced array methods.\n699: **Source:** context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:28\n700: \n701: ### DOM (Document Object Model)\n702: **Definition:** Programming interface for HTML documents that represents the page structure as a tree of objects.\n703: **Source:** context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:20\n704: \n705: ### Reactive Data Binding\n706: **Definition:** Automatic synchronization between data model and user interface elements.\n707: **Source:** context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:54\n708: \n709: ### CSS Grid\n710: **Definition:** Two-dimensional layout system for creating responsive grid-based page layouts.\n711: **Source:** context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:39\n712: \n713: ### Progressive Enhancement\n714: **Definition:** Web design strategy that provides basic functionality to all users while enhancing experience for those with modern browsers.\n715: **Source:** context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:150\n716: \n717: ## Open Questions\n718: \n719: ### OQ-01: Character Selection Criteria\n720: **Question:** What specific criteria should be used for selecting the 8 classic Star Wars Lego characters?\n721: **Impact on:** FR-01 (Character Gallery Display)\n722: **Source Context:** Only specified \"classic Star Wars Lego characters\" without selection guidelines.\n723: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:40-44\n724: \n725: ### OQ-02: Learning Assessment Methods\n726: **Question:** How should the application measure and validate that users are actually learning JavaScript concepts?\n727: **Impact on:** KPI-02 (Concept Demonstration Effectiveness)\n728: **Source Context:** Educational objectives stated but assessment methods not defined.\n729: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:16-21\n730: \n731: ### OQ-03: State Persistence Strategy\n732: **Question:** Should user preferences (likes, greetings) persist beyond the current session using local storage?\n733: **Impact on:** FR-03 (Character Like/Favorite System), FR-05 (Personalized Greeting System)\n734: **Source Context:** Session persistence mentioned but cross-session strategy unclear.\n735: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:50-58\n736: \n737: ### OQ-04: Character Information Content\n738: **Question:** What specific information should be displayed for each character when selected (FR-07)?\n739: **Impact on:** FR-07 (Interactive Character Selection)\n740: **Source Context:** \"Additional information\" mentioned but content not specified.\n741: source: context-pack/project-overview.md#lines:40-44\n742: \n743: ### OQ-05: Error Handling Scenarios\n744: **Question:** What specific error scenarios should be anticipated and how should they be handled gracefully?\n745: **Impact on:** NFR-05 (Client-Side Security), multiple FRs\n746: **Source Context:** Security and validation requirements mentioned but specific error scenarios not detailed.\n747: source: context-pack/technical-requirements.md#lines:155-162", "metadata": {"start_line": 500, "end_line": 747, "returned_lines": 248, "has_more": false, "eof_reached": false, "truncated": false}}}
